{"id":2341,"date":"2017-10-17T12:44:51","date_gmt":"2017-10-17T12:44:51","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/screening.mhanational.org\/article\/i-dont-want-to-leave-my-room\/"},"modified":"2023-11-17T10:56:16","modified_gmt":"2023-11-17T15:56:16","slug":"i-dont-want-leave-my-room","status":"publish","type":"article","link":"https:\/\/screening.mhanational.org\/content\/i-dont-want-leave-my-room\/","title":{"rendered":"I don&#8217;t want to leave my room"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Sometimes the outside world seems too overwhelming.\u00a0 It can feel like something is physically preventing you from moving. Like there\u2019s nothing worth getting out of bed for or <a href=\"https:\/\/screening.mhanational.org\/content\/i-cant-deal-pressure-and-expectations\/\">there&#8217;s too much to do<\/a>. Or even like as if the world is too loud or you don\u2019t belong. Shame, obligations, work, school, or relationships can make you want to sit out of everything.<\/p>\n<p>Isolation, exhaustion, and lack of motivation or interest in life are common experiences of individuals struggling with stress, <a href=\"https:\/\/screening.mhanational.org\/depression\/\">depression<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/screening.mhanational.org\/anxiety\/\">anxiety<\/a>, and <a href=\"https:\/\/screening.mhanational.org\/mental-health-101\/\">other mental health conditions<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>You don\u2019t have to <a href=\"https:\/\/screening.mhanational.org\/content\/i-feel-guilty-about-being-depressed\/\">feel guilty for having a very human experience or struggling<\/a>. Sometimes the very best we can do is get through one minute at a time under the blankets in our rooms. Even if the negative thoughts and sensations feel like the only thing in the world right now, know that eventually they do pass.<\/p>\n<div class=\"layout-action show-actions_h\"><div class=\"diy-tool-shortcode embed-type-full\">\t\n<div class=\"wrap full no-margin-mobile diy-tool-container\" id=\"diy-tool-145629_1\">\t\n    <form class=\"d